tags: why is tony not given credit for this
title: tony deserves credit
body:
so in the wake of endgame/trailer hype, i’ve been re-watching movies, and i was just watching avengers.

everyone hyper fixates on the ‘doth mother know you weareth her drapes’ but fail to realize that after that scene tony holds his own and even matches thor in battle. 

admittedly thor isn’t at his strongest (duh), but at that time he was still really powerful, and tony matches him in battle with one of his early suits! like that raw power deserves to be recognized

summary: Rewatched Civil War, and it made me realize that this movie is like watching a really nasty divorce.
body:
Rewatched Civil War, and it made me realize that this movie is like watching a really nasty divorce.

The parents are fighting, add a presumed dead exlover into the mix, as well as a secret to break them up even more, and get the kids dragged into the fight being forced to pick sides.

In the end, one gets full custody of the kids (except the baby, cause the other parent gets him), and the other keeps the house and money.

TELL ME I’M NOT THE ONLY ONE WHO THOUGHT IT LIKE THAT!!!
